Triad Networks

Tim Vigers

24 May 2020

CIT Package

Using a threshold of p < 0.05 for the omnibus CIT test, there are 141 unique pairs with significant mediation. Within these pairs, there are 124 unique probes and 10 unique metabolites.

MCMC

# MCMC parameters
n_adapt = 1000
iter = 10000
# Example nodes
methyl = "cg00339319"
metab = "gctof_33"
temp = pair_data[,c("T1Dgroup",methyl,metab)]
temp = temp[complete.cases(temp),]
temp$T1Dgroup = ifelse(temp$T1Dgroup == "T1D control",0,1)
# data for jags
N = nrow(temp)
jags_data = list(t1d=c(temp[,"T1Dgroup"]),methyl=c(temp[,methyl]),
                 metab=c(temp[,metab]),
                 N=N)
# JAGS
mod = jags.model("./code/jags/struct2.jags",
                 data = jags_data, n.adapt = n_adapt,n.chains = 2,quiet = T)
# MCMC
dic = dic.samples(mod,n.iter = iter,thin = 20)
dic_tot = round(sum(dic$deviance) + sum(dic$penalty),1)
